  "text": "All the linear classifers described in Subsection 2 requires the storage of p + 1 parameters (p weights and one bias). The MLP and ELM networks, each, require the storage of (p+1)·q+(q+1)·c parameters, which is a much higher requirement than that of linear neural classifiers. Hence, between a linear and a nonlinear neural classifier with similar recognition rates, one should choose the linear one. Details about the time complexity of the adaptive filtering algorithms used by the classifiers described previously can be found in [CITATION_1] .",
